Horseshoe Falls , also known as Canadian Falls , is one of three waterfalls which collectively form Niagara Falls on the Niagara River along the Canada-US Border .
Approximately 90 % of the Niagara River , after diversions for hydropower generation , flows over Horseshoe Falls .
The remaining 10 % flows over American Falls and Bridal Veil falls .
It is located between Terrapin Point on Goat Island in the US state of New York , and Table Rock in the Canadian province of Ontario .